{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-10844/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-10844"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:08:44"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman yells at a man across from her."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-10844","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-10844"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/canvas/1/722a9a44-833d-4240-a176-281bef17a160","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:14:45.063Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Once they sit down to eat, Reynolds and Alma are seen exclusively in single shots, emphasizing the tension between them at this point in their relationship. However, Reynolds’s shots are dirty singles with pieces of Alma remaining in frame. This choice emphasizes two things: on the one hand, it gives visual representation to how Reynolds feels crowded out by Alma in his life and house. On the other, it functions as another example of how Alma’s role in this plot is subverted; she is, in fact, not the docile figure that one might expect in a story of toxic masculinity. She remains in the frame even when the focus is on Reynolds, much as she ultimately wields greater power than might be expected.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10844/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:713.7837837837831,144.28629699391388,488.92173423423424,570.016891891892"}}}]}]}]}